"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-07-cuba-wrestler-lopezs-hometown-cheers-historic-olympic-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"HERRADURA,\\u00a0Cuba\\u00a0(AFP) - In the rural Cuban town of Herradura, scores of family members and friends took the day off work Tuesday to watch wrestler\\u00a0Mijain\\u00a0Lopez\\u00a0make Olympic history with a fifth successive gold medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 15, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 2.0752353077492358e-11, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 51, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"score\": 0.9999983952429063, \"rank\": 1.4460991561328143e-06, \"text\": \"Herradura\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How amazing!\\\"\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"his mother Leonor Nunez said, bursting into tears when her son defeated Chile's\\u00a0Yasmani Acosta in the 130kg Greco-Roman final.\", \"from\": 233, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"score\": 0.9277977879863022, \"rank\": 0.07780976865184881, \"text\": \"Chile\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yasmani Acosta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\"}, {\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6428419814813004e-26, \"text\": \"Greco-Roman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_wrestling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was expecting it because all of Herradura was waiting for that medal,\\\" the 66-year-old said after gathering her emotions.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"score\": 0.9999983952429063, \"rank\": 1.4460991561328143e-06, \"text\": \"Herradura\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheers and applause erupted after the match at the watching party in the small mountain-ringed town, made up of humble homes and dusty streets, 140 kilometres (87 miles) from the capital Havana.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.444654839608728e-15, \"text\": \"Havana\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is here that\\u00a0Mijain, who turns 42 in two weeks, honed his prodigious physique working in the fields during his childhood.\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was discovered by a wrestling coach at eight-years-old and joined the Cuban team at 17.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Tuesday, he beat the likes of sprinter Carl Lewis and swimmers Michael Phelps and Katie Ledecky to become the only person to win individual gold medals in five consecutive Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.211800476940547e-33, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Cuban flag flutters from the antenna on the roof of his home, where some 100 people gathered to watch the fight in the courtyard.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Cuba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cuban flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nunez told AFP that she spoke to her son on Monday night before the fight to advise him, as she had for every major duel of his career.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999997338409584, \"rank\": 2.65755187354241e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I told him that they are both Cuban, but that Yasmani represents Chile.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 1428, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"score\": 0.9277977879863022, \"rank\": 0.07780976865184881, \"text\": \"Chile\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have been lifelong friends, so he should apologise off the mat, but on the mat, he has to win,\\\" she said firmly.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The excitement was palpable in Herradura in the lead-up to the fight, with his family waiting from early in the day under a thatched-roof structure decorated with a huge poster of\\u00a0Lopez.\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"score\": 0.9999983952429063, \"rank\": 1.4460991561328143e-06, \"text\": \"Herradura\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldo Moreno, a 52-year-old rice farmer, left his plot to enjoy the moment with his neighbours.\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today he takes the fifth, that victory goes to Herradura.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"score\": 0.9999983952429063, \"rank\": 1.4460991561328143e-06, \"text\": \"Herradura\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tequila_Herradura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a sporting glory,\\\" said an emotional Moreno, who has known the wrestler since he was a child.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He recalls\\u00a0Lopez\\u00a0promising in 2023 that \\\"he will dedicate that fight to his deceased father\\\".\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fighter's mother ordered a candle to be lit for her husband Bartolo\\u00a0Lopez, whose photograph was placed on an altar to accompany them on the crucial day.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\", \"score\": 0.9997898262647742, \"rank\": 0.00011065604632143724, \"text\": \"Lopez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is a great honour that he is a son of this town,\\\" said Hilario Hernandez, 64, who wandered over on horseback to take part in the event, in the town of about 10,000 inhabitants.\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2310, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilario_(footballer,_born_1905)\", \"score\": 0.9479947370542557, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hilario\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilario_(footballer,_born_1905)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilario_(footballer,_born_1905)\"}, {\"begin\": 2318, \"end\": 2327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hernandez_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.7544329697359324, \"rank\": 0.12361940355195014, \"text\": \"Hernandez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hernandez_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hernandez_(wrestler)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cuban President Miguel Diaz-Canel also congratulated the five-time Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Cuba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cuban President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_D\\u00edaz-Canel\", \"score\": 0.999999811474499, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Miguel Diaz-Canel\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_D\\u00edaz-Canel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_D\\u00edaz-Canel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thank you\\u00a0Mijain, for your loyalty, your talent, your dedication.\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for the gold of your heart as a Cuban warrior,\\\" the president wrote on X.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When, just shy of his 39th birthday, the Cuban giant overcame the Georgian Iakobi Kajaia in the 130kg competition in the COVID-delayed Tokyo Games three years ago, it was widely expected to be his swansong.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had not competed since and had to fight to get his weight below the required 130kg.\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's my idol, my friend and my rival too.\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I am going to enjoy this fight a lot,\\\" said his Paris rival, Yasmani Acosta, 36, who was born in Cuba, in the run-up to the fight.\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999536158, \"rank\": 4.633506769248863e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3074, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yasmani Acosta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\"}, {\"begin\": 3110, \"end\": 3114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 2.0752353077492358e-11, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Acosta fled the communist island nation while in Chile in 2015 after a tournament with the Cuban squad.\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"score\": 0.9277977879863022, \"rank\": 0.07780976865184881, \"text\": \"Chile\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\"}, {\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9820896073816229, \"rank\": 0.01823702364107414, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years later he told journalists that it was the most difficult decision of his life.\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He had to work as a security guard in nightclubs, until he was given Chilean nationality and allowed to compete for the country.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3409, \"end\": 3416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"score\": 0.8708826953150997, \"rank\": 0.14123775250496035, \"text\": \"Chilean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": []}]}"